version: "2.0.0"

agents:
  - name: "selfharm"
    priority: 0
    label_name: "SELF_HARM"
    prompt_url: "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ucsd-ets/tritongpt-sitemaps/main/prompts/agent-selfharm.yml"
    response: |
      If you are going through a crisis, please know that help is available. We encourage you to connect with one of the following resources for support:

      *   **For Registered UC San Diego Students:**

          *   **Counseling and Psychological Services (CAPS)**: For urgent support, call (858) 534-3755 and outside business hours, select option 2.

          *   Visit the [CAPS website](https://caps.ucsd.edu) for more information.

      *   **Additional Resources:**

          *   [24-Hour Suicide and Crisis Lifeline](https://988lifeline.org/): Dial 988 if you or someone you care about is experiencing suicidal thoughts.

          *   [It's Up to Us SD](https://up2sd.org/): Access & Crisis Line (888) 724-7240 or Live Chat.

          *   [Crisis Text Line](https://www.crisistextline.org/): Text HOME to 741741 from anywhere in the USA, anytime, 24/7 or message in What'sApp.

      [CalHOPE Connect](https://www.calhopeconnect.org/): For anonymous, non-emergency mental and emotional support. Live Chat or in CA call (833) 317-4673.

